Script(s) to tie git and jira through Jira issues and git branches.

To use the git_jira.sh script through a git alias, put git_jira.sh
somewhere, then execute a shell command like this:

% git config --global alias.jira '!/home/me/bin/git_jira.sh'

You will need to specify the location of the Jira CLI jar file,
the Jira server, your Jira user, and Jira password.  The script
will prompt you for these (and save them) if you do not provide
them in the config file.  To set them in your config file:

% git config --global jira.jar <path_to_jar>
% git config --global jira.server <url for Jira server>
% git config --global jira.user <Your Jira user id>
% git config --global jira.password <Your Jira password>

Then, if you like, set default project, component, and issue type:

% git config --global jira.component Component1
% git config --global jira.project MyProject
% git config --global jira.issuetype Bug

Then you can open a Jira issue and create a git branch based on
the name of the issue:

% git jira open -s "Fix login permissions in user script"
git branch MyProject-31233 created

When done working on the issue, you can resolve it with:

% git jira close <issue id>
